Package arcade.patch.env.component

Class PatchComponentRemodel

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.env.component.PatchComponentRemodel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Component, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
    public class PatchComponentRemodel
extends java.lang.Object
implements Component
    Implementation of Component for remodeling edges.

    This component can only be used with PatchComponentSitesGraph. The component is stepped every REMODELING_INTERVAL ticks. The radius and wall thickness of edges are remodeled as a function of shear stress (SCALE_SHEAR), circumferential stress ( SCALE_CIRCUM), flow rate (SCALE_FLOW), and metabolic demand (SCALE_METABOLIC). The scaling based on shear (tau) and circumferential (sigma) stress mainly affect radius mid and area mass, respectively, but can also affect the other term (SCALE_SIGMA and SCALE_TAU). Edges that are below a minimum wall thickness or radius are removed from the graph. All hemodynamic properties are recalculated at the end of the step.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • SCALE_FLOW = flow rate scaling
